    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 1. Webhook\nEntry point for the system. Receives the Excel file uploaded by the user from the v0 frontend as a binary POST request. Response mode is set to wait until the full workflow completes before sending anything back.",
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "7d00ebd6-d082-43f5-bf5e-98a406782887",
      "name": "Sticky Note 1",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        4400,
        944
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 2. Extract from File\nConverts the binary Excel file into individual JSON items, one per row. Each item contains prospect_name, prospect_title, and company_name. The AI Agent will process each row independently.",
        "height": 192,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "6cc7fac2-9ca9-4e4a-a2d7-36494021689e",
      "name": "Sticky Note 2",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        4752,
        752
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 3. AI Agent\nThe brain of the workflow. For each prospect row, it calls the Customer_Research tool to gather live signals, then generates a structured meeting prep brief using the system prompt. Runs once per prospect.",
        "height": 192,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "421e4ead-4700-43c6-a133-eb6441a61884",
      "name": "Sticky Note 3",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        5024,
        752
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 4. OpenAI Chat Model\nPowers the AI Agent. Using GPT but you can swap in any LLM supported by n8n, Claude, Gemini, or Mistral. Connect your API credentials here.",
        "height": 188,
        "width": 256,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "46fa65bf-6f32-4370-8c65-cdb2d341dfcc",
      "name": "Sticky Note 4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        4832,
        1312
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 5. Prospect_Research\nTavily search tool connected to the AI Agent. The agent decides what to search for using $fromAI. Returns recent news, funding rounds, hires, and product signals to inform the brief. Add your TAVILY_API_KEY in n8n Variables.",
        "height": 192,
        "width": 288,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "ff8afa65-cf19-4cb6-b228-fa438fb6ad53",
      "name": "Sticky Note 5",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        5184,
        1312
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 6. Edit Fields\nCleans up the AI Agent output into 4 labeled columns: prospect_name, prospect_title, company_name, and brief. Maps the raw output field to the friendly brief column name ready for Excel.",
        "height": 192,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "b49c7d30-80b2-4451-9396-82f99a5688a0",
      "name": "Sticky Note 6",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        5296,
        752
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 7. Convert to File\nTakes the cleaned JSON rows and converts them back into a valid Excel binary file. Output is stored in the data binary field, ready to be sent back to the frontend.",
        "height": 172,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "e4d78ff2-702a-43e1-ab1e-8d35db115f43",
      "name": "Sticky Note 7",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        5456,
        1120
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 8. Respond to Webhook\nSends the Excel binary back to the v0 frontend as the webhook response. Content-Type and Content-Disposition headers tell the browser to treat the response as a file download, not JSON.",
        "height": 176,
        "width": 304,
        "color": 4
